<dl id="n03066e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03066e">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03066e"> 66(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> rest assured ~ <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n03066e"><li>FW 442.16 </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/lexqA.htm#n03066e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/qA/l39qA.htm#n03066e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n03066e">MS BL 47482b-15v</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:032 <a name="qA1d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA1d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qA1d.htm#n03066e">Draft: III&sect;2A.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Letter from RW to MW, Zurich, 17 March 1853]</font> &ldquo;LADY, &mdash; God henceforth will protect you from my rude manners &hellip; If, in future, I impose upon myself more frequent acts of self-denial &hellip; <mark>rest assured</mark> that this is because I am determined, above all else, to obtain forgiveness &hellip;&rdquo; &hellip; Here may be seen a characteristic peculiar to Wagner, that subtle art of reproaching through self-accusation <small> Edouard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESWI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ESWI"><cite title="source">Woman: the Inspirer</cite></a>, trans. by Fred Rothwell (1918) 9-10</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
